[tab]if you deny what you are, that’s enough to 
[tab]keep you from moving forward.
[sync][wait][clear][end]

msg_8:
[tab]What is your "self" as far as you all are concerned?
[choice(2)]An irreplaceable treasure. Right?
That which brings about doubt and suffering...
[end_choice][clear][end]

msg_9:
[color(yellow)]Sakya[color(white)]
[tab]Do you think so? 
[tab]As I thought, like your name implies, 
[tab]it appears you are still trapped by "Maya".
[wait][clear][end]

msg_10:
[color(yellow)]Sakya[color(white)]
[tab]By all rights, one should discover 
[tab]the state of Anatta by oneself, 
[tab]but I shall extend a helping hand to you.
[sync][wait][clear][end]

msg_11:
[color(yellow)]Sakya[color(white)]
[tab]Precisely. It is the egotism of gaining attachment to 
[tab]imprisonment by the non-existent illusion called "I" that 
[tab]ultimately brings suffering to yourself and the world.
[wait][clear][end]

msg_12:
[color(yellow)]Sakya[color(white)]
[tab]"All things lack inherent identity."
[wait][clear][end]

msg_13:
[color(yellow)]Sakya[color(white)]
[tab]Remember to accept that everything in this transient 
[tab]world changes from having no substance to having 
[tab]substance on the basis of dependent origination. 
[wait][clear][color(yellow)]Sakya[color(white)]
[tab]This understanding is what will bring 
[tab]an end to suffering.
[wait][clear][end]

msg_14:
